name: PHVS_Industry_NAICS_2007
title: Industry (NAICS)
description: The North American Industry Classification System (NAICS) consists of a set of six digit codes that classify and categorize industries.  It also organizes the categories on a production/process-oriented basis.  This new, uniform, industry-wide classification system has been designed as the index for statistical reporting of all economic activities of the U.S., Canada, and Mexico.
